READ.ME (see also Docker Hub):

This is a mysql graphical user interface for accessing mysql/mariadb databases in the same docker network.

It's using alpine linux, php and nginx to run the adminer.php script on port 5080.

See: https://www.adminer.org/

To run it, execute: docker run -d -p 127.0.0.1:5080:5080 mat10243x/adminer

Open http://localhost:5080 and fill in your database credentials and the ip number of the server running the database (e.g. for the host 172.17.0.1) to connect to the database.
